<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="39" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1323,1159,1905]" pageId="10" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis box="[264,383,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="39">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: Wall concrescent, thin, made of radiating rods connected by chitinous material, elliptical in outline; ribs on shell absent; heath absent. Basis membranous. Scutum and tergum not fused, scutum transversally elongated, tergum triangular.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[312,871,1279,1305]" pageId="10" pageNumber="39" type="materials_examined">
